I'mmmmmmm BAAAAACCCCCCKKK!!!<br><br>
I will also be trying to write up a short story, for that section, of how I see the war affecting me, but also affecting all of our country, and scars and wounds that continue still, for combatants and resistors.  Most of us agree that the war was a mistake and I will not continue to beat you over the head with that historically correct fact. Rather I'd welcome dialogue on impact, impact on our lives since the war.  My becoming a shrink, who for years seemed to have been specializing in working with police officers (who were all ex nam vets-having changed one uniform for another and find that 20 years later they are fired and burned out), can say the the war led to my shrinkdom. 25 years later to my own burn out too.  Now I just am a cyber-shrink and constant critic.   <br><br>
